# Biogrix Coding Style

## Language

- **JavaScript only**. No TypeScript. No `.ts` or `.tsx` files.

## Functions

- Keep functions **small and focused** (ideally under 30 lines)
- One clear responsibility per function
- Prefer pure functions when possible

## Readability

- Write **clean, readable code** over clever or terse solutions
- Use descriptive variable and function names
- Avoid abbreviations unless widely understood

## Logic Structure

- **Avoid deeply nested logic** (max 2-3 levels when possible)
- Extract nested blocks into named functions
- Use early returns to reduce nesting

## Comments

- Add **helpful comments** for non-obvious logic
- Document "why" not "what" when the code is self-explanatory
- Keep comments up to date with code changes
